→ Increasing urbanization, especially in less-developed regions, is a significant megatrend. In this context, the demand for more sustainable and efficient products, technologies, and solutions – including passenger trans- portation and access to renewable energy – continues to grow as more and more people move to cities.

→ As global population growth progresses at a slower pace, our societies are aging, and an increasing number of people need medical care. This demographic change is also contributing to a shortage of workers across industries.